 deference to the deputies at his side lauded for letting his people do what they do best he is the very antithesis of a micromanager but when it comes to the really big decisions — such as whether to spend  billion per year on the nfl or  million on nascar — bodenheimer sets the table both with his subordinates and the top brass at disney all seven of bodenheimer’s direct reports — a group that was shuffled somewhat in an october restructuring — get their share of the spotlight and are often the public faces of the company but they all are following a strategic vision that is set and subtly championed by the mildmannered bodenheimer “when george sets a goal he just steadfastly keeps marching forward” said nascar vice president of broadcasting dick glover who was once a top programming executive at espn “that’s why he is so successful” there’s a certain level of irony that bodenheimer would be the most influential person in of all businesses sports sports is a business dominated by largerthanlife characters such as phil knight and david stern people who ooze charisma and some would say genius bodenheimer would be described as congenial kind and yes smart but you’ll probably never see him standing in a bathrobe in an espn ad one could argue that the espn brand and bodenheimer are exact opposites one is brash flashy and a little acerbic the other is deferential lowkey and well just kind of nice “he’s such a good listener” said adam silver president of nba entertainment “he’s content to be the most interested person in the room rather than the most interesting” however when you ask “what is espn” the answers today point to many things that quietly are quintessential bodenheimer espn is multiplexes of cable channels well that started with bodenheimer who is largely credited with the launch and growth of espn when he was head of affiliate sales espn is multiple platforms well that’s been bodenheimer’s rallying cry since the start of the decade espn is emerging technology well the new digital broadcast center espn hd mobile espn — groundbreaking initiatives that put espn firmly on the cusp of emerging media — are the sort of things that don’t happen without a president’s personal advocacy and espn is bigtime sports television with bigtime price tags under bodenheimer espn had rights to all four of the major pro leagues for the first time one could argue that it still has the big four television sports with nascar dwarfing hockey add in the pga tour three out of four tennis grand slam events and all but two of the major college football conferences and espn has a dominance that perhaps no media outlet has in any entertainment sector bodenheimer will always lead through consensus surrounded by elitelevel thinkers and dealmakers through that bottomup approach he leads not only espn and abc sports but the sports industry at large microsoft personalized ad preferences to opt out of personalized ads in this browser your browser history must allow firstparty and thirdparty cookies and you must have your browsing experience set to not delete browsing history on exit instructions for enabling cookies and configuring your browsing history may be available in your browsers settings privacy or help documentation sign in hold on… we’re sorry but this didn’t work you can’t turn off personalized ads right now because your browser is currently blocking thirdparty cookies we can help you fix this issue let’s get started depending on what browser you use open options or settings make sure that thirdparty cookies are not blocked anymore to find out how search your browser’s help revisit httpchoicemicrosoftcomoptout and then on the “personalized ads in this browser” tile click off ext about our ads to create a more customized online experience some of the ads you may receive on microsoft websites and apps are tailored to your previous activities searches and site visits youre in control and heres where you can make the advertising choice thats right fo